headline: Formula 1 Stock Is in Pole Position for Even More Gains
summary: Shareholders in Formula One, which is part of John Malone’s Liberty Media empire, are a lap ahead.  Both its tracking stocks—the Class A  FWONA  shares, which have voting rights, and the more actively traded Class C FWONK shares, which don’t—are up more than 12% this year.  The sport’s popularity has been steadily rising in recent years thanks to the  Netflix  reality show Drive to Survive, which is now in its seventh season.
